Reporting to the Meter Operations Management Manager, the successful candidate will be responsible in the daily operation and monitoring of the Automatic Meter Retrieval (AMR) system of all WESM metering installations in Luzon, Visayas and Mindanao (LuzViMin). The position is mainly accountable for the following:
Daily meter data retrieval and transmittal to the Market Operator, NGCPs billing system and Trading participants using the AMR system of NGCP;
Monitor of the daily operational status, asset health condition and ongoing maintenance;
Proper management of Masterfile, TIM files and other similar requirements of the AMR system of NGCP;
Pre-commissioning test and corrective maintenance work on AMR connectivity requirements to al WESM metering installations in LuzViMin;
Validation of meter data and preparation of estimation and editing requirements as prescribed by the WESM Rules and Metering Manual to ensure integrity and readiness of metered quantities for billing and settlement;
Preparation of the monthly energy balance report which serves as the basis of Luzon, Visayas and Mindanao Grid's system loss data of NGCP;
Coordinates with the Overall Command Center on the status of metering installation maintenance activities.
Performs the required meter data validation, estimation and editing process and submit the recommended meter data to the Market Operator in accordance to the methodologies and procedures prescribed by the WESM Rules and Metering manual;
Ensures the operational compliance of NGCP’s AMR system to WESM, Philippine Grid Code (PGC), and Energy Regulatory Commission (ERC) regulatory requirements

Requirements:
Bachelor’s Degree in Electrical Engineering
Licensed Electrical Engineer
Three (3) years of relevant experience
Knowledge in Electrical Methodology and Metering
Knowledge of Microsoft Office applications (Word, Excel, PPT)
Effective collaborative skills with other functional groups, external customers and government regulating agencies


